Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Quarter the @lime{1}. Cut the @tomato{2} into 1cm cubes.

Trim the @cucumber{1} and halve lengthways. Thinly slice widthways.

Pat the @prawns{150%grams} dry with #kitchen paper{}, transfer to a #bowl{}
and season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw prawns.

Toss with one-third of the @aioli{1%sachet} then coat with the @breadcrumbs{1%pack}.

Place a #pan{} over medium-high heat with a knob of @butter{to taste}.

Fry the prawns until cooked through, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Pop the @tortilla{8} into the oven to warm, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> TIP: Fry any unused breadcrumbs along with the prawns to use later as garnish.

Divide the cucumber and tomato between the tortillas.

Place the prawns on top and drizzle over remaining aioli.

Serve with the lime wedges alongside for squeezing over.